{"title":"Lenovo updates ThinkPad lineup with 16:10 screens and more","link":"https://arstechnica.com/?p=1744328","date":1614109121000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><header><h4>Ryzen â€”</h4><h2 itemprop=\"description\">The new laptops launch this spring.</h2></header><div itemprop=\"articleBody\"><div><ul><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/01_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Hero_Front_Facing-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/01_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Hero_Front_Facing.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/01_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Hero_Front_Facing-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/01_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Hero_Front_Facing-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744551\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744551\"><span></span><p>The front of the ThinkPad X13.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/06_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Hero_Left_Side_15_Degree_Screen_Open-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/06_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Hero_Left_Side_15_Degree_Screen_Open.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/06_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Hero_Left_Side_15_Degree_Screen_Open-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/06_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Hero_Left_Side_15_Degree_Screen_Open-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744552\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744552\"><span></span><p>One side of the ThinkPad X13.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Tour_Right_Side_Profile-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Tour_Right_Side_Profile.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Tour_Right_Side_Profile-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_13X_Gen_2_Tour_Right_Side_Profile-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744553\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744553\"><span></span><p>The other side of the ThinkPad X13.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/06_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Hero_Front_Facing_Right-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/06_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Hero_Front_Facing_Right.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/06_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Hero_Front_Facing_Right-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/06_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Hero_Front_Facing_Right-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744554\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744554\"><span></span><p>The front of the ThinkPad X13 Yoga.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Hero_Tent_B-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Hero_Tent_B.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Hero_Tent_B-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Hero_Tent_B-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744555\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744555\"><span></span><p>The ThinkPad X13 Yoga in a convertible configuration.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/16_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Tour_Left_Profile-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/16_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Tour_Left_Profile.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/16_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Tour_Left_Profile-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/16_Thinkpad_X13_Yoga_G2_Tour_Left_Profile-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744556\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744556\"><span></span><p>One side of the ThinkPad X13 Yoga.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li></ul></div><p>Today, Lenovo announced a broad overhaul of its ThinkPad laptop lineup, led by the popular X13 and X13 Yoga.</p><p>Lenovo has added many features previously seen in its X1 Nano model to various other laptops across the ThinkPad line. Among those is a continuing shift to 16:10 displays, which most productivity users will greatly appreciate compared to the more media-focused 16:9 aspect ratio found in recent prior models.</p><p>There's also human-presence detection; the laptops use a radar sensor to detect when you're sitting down in front of them, and they wake up accordingly. And of course, like so many similar laptops in this day and age, you can get these machines with fingerprint readers built into the power buttons now.</p><p>As for specs, CPU options for the X13 and X13 Yoga include Tiger Lake (11th Gen) Intel Core chips with optional vPro, plus AMD Ryzen 5000 options.&nbsp;A big focus of this refresh is bridging the previously existing gap in features between the Intel and AMD configurations, now that interest is particularly high in AMD's processors. We're not 100 percent to parity, but we're closer than before.</p><p>The X13 and X13 Yoga have 13.3-inch displays at either 1920x1200 or 2560x1600, Finally, the redesign includes wider touchpads, Wi-Fi 6E, and in the X13 only, optional sub-6 5G support.</p><p>Lenovo also overhauled the T-series lineup.&nbsp;The new T-series laptops still have 16:9 displays, though that admittedly makes a bit more sense for laptops that offer 4K Dolby Vision display configurations, discrete graphics, and other specs and features oriented around media consumption.</p><div><ul><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T14_Hero_Front_Facing_JD_INTEL-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T14_Hero_Front_Facing_JD_INTEL.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T14_Hero_Front_Facing_JD_INTEL-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T14_Hero_Front_Facing_JD_INTEL-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744557\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744557\"><span></span><p>The front of the ThinkPad T14.</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T14_Tour_Left_Profile_INTEL-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T14_Tour_Left_Profile_INTEL.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T14_Tour_Left_Profile_INTEL-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T14_Tour_Left_Profile_INTEL-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744558\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744558\"><span></span><p>One side of the ThinkPad T14.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T14_Tour_Right_Profile_INTEL-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T14_Tour_Right_Profile_INTEL.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T14_Tour_Right_Profile_INTEL-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T14_Tour_Right_Profile_INTEL-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744559\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744559\"><span></span><p>The other side of the ThinkPad T14.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Black_Hero_Front_Facing_JD-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Black_Hero_Front_Facing_JD.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Black_Hero_Front_Facing_JD-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Black_Hero_Front_Facing_JD-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744560\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744560\"><span></span><p>The front of the ThinkPad T14s.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Tour_Right_Side_Profile-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Tour_Right_Side_Profile.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Tour_Right_Side_Profile-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Tour_Right_Side_Profile-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744561\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744561\"><span></span><p>One side of the ThinkPad T14s.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Tour_Left_Side_Profile-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Tour_Left_Side_Profile.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Tour_Left_Side_Profile-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T14s_Gen_2_Tour_Left_Side_Profile-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744562\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744562\"><span></span><p>The other side of the ThinkPad T14s.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T15_Hero_Front_Facing_JD-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T15_Hero_Front_Facing_JD.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T15_Hero_Front_Facing_JD-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/02_Thinkpad_T15_Hero_Front_Facing_JD-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744563\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744563\"><span></span><p>The front of the ThinkPad T15.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T15_Tour_Left_Profile-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T15_Tour_Left_Profile.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T15_Tour_Left_Profile-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/11_Thinkpad_T15_Tour_Left_Profile-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744564\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744564\"><span></span><p>One side of the ThinkPad T15.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li><li data-thumb=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T15_Tour_Right_Profile-150x150.png\" data-src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T15_Tour_Right_Profile.png\" data-responsive=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T15_Tour_Right_Profile-980x980.png 1080, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/12_Thinkpad_T15_Tour_Right_Profile-1440x1440.png 2560\" data-sub-html=\"#caption-1744565\"><figure><figcaption id=\"caption-1744565\"><span></span><p>The other side of the ThinkPad T15.</p><p><span></span> Lenovo</p></figcaption></figure></li></ul></div><p>The T14 and T14s have 14-inch displays, and the 15 has a 15.6-inch display. CPU options offer 11th-Gen Core i7 CPUs (also with vPro options) or, alternatively, AMD Ryzen 5000 Pro. Intel versions of various new Thinkpad laptops have an \"i\" after the nameâ€”as in, Lenovo ThinkPad T14 i. The AMD versions don't.</p><p>Across the T series lineup, you'll find Wi-Fi 6 or 6E, 4G and 5G configurations, and FullHD webcamsâ€”though many features are optional or not default when you configure the devices.&nbsp;Here are the starting prices and availability dates for each of the T and X series laptops:</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Model</th><th>Availability</th><th>Starting price</th></tr><tr><td><strong>ThinkPad T14s i</strong></td><td>March 2021</td><td>$1,499</td></tr><tr><td><strong>ThinkPad T14s</strong></td><td>May 2021</td><td>$1,279</td></tr><tr><td><strong>ThinkPad T14 i</strong></td><td>March 2021</td><td>$1,379</td></tr><tr><td><strong>ThinkPad T14</strong></td><td>May 2021</td><td>$1,159</td></tr><tr><td><b>ThinkPad T15</b></td><td>March 2021</td><td>$1,379</td></tr><tr><td><strong>ThinkPad X13 Yoga</strong></td><td>April 2021</td><td>$1,379</td></tr><tr><td><strong>ThinkPad X13 i</strong></td><td>March 2021</td><td>$1,299</td></tr><tr><td><strong>ThinkPad X13</strong></td><td>May 2021</td><td>$1,139</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Other updated products include the L14, L15, and PL14s, as well as a new monitor carrying the P40w label. If you're interested in those models, you can learn more at <a href=\"https://news.lenovo.com/pressroom/press-releases/latest-thinkpad-portfolio-ready-to-do-business-anywhere/\">Lenovo's website</a>.</p><p><em>Listing image by <a href=\"https://www.lenovo.com/us/en/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lenovo</a></em></p></div></div></div>","author":"Samuel Axon","siteTitle":"Ars Technica","siteHash":"5b0d